`★ Insight ─────────────────────────────────────`
**Why `cubeStacking.ts` duplicates placement validation:** The `canPlaceCubeCheck` helper (line 433) duplicates the logic from `cubePlacement.ts:canPlaceCube`. This is intentional — `getPlacementPreview` is a pure function that takes an `occupiedSlots: Set<string>` parameter, so it doesn't depend on `cubePlacement`'s module-level registry. This keeps the preview computation side-effect-free and independently testable.

**Callback injection pattern:** `placeHeldCube` takes 4 function parameters instead of importing directly from `grabber.ts` and `cubePlacement.ts`. This avoids circular dependencies (grabber already imports from cubeStacking) and makes tests trivial — just pass `jest.fn()` stubs.
